widgets_values: A captivating historical scene depicting a general in golden plated armor, pouring red wine from a cup over a detailed map spread across a large wooden table. The map is marked with various strategic points and geographical features. The general's soldiers, dressed in traditional medieval attire, surround the table, with a mix of astonishment, concern, and resolve on their faces. The background shows a dimly lit castle chamber, with torches and candles casting flickering shadows. The overall atmosphere is tense and dramatic, as the soldiers try to understand the unconventional battle plan.

UPDATED VERSION! Ultimate


ONLY PROMPT FROM THE WILDCARD NODE!


WILDCARD NODE:

<Populate> mode allows you to prompt into the upper box, and automatically gets info from Wildcards (you cannot edit the lower box in this mode).

<Fixed> mode allows you to prompt normally in the lower box.

============================================

LORAS: 

You'll need to put the triggers into the Wildcard node.

SET RESOLUTION MODE:

If you want to use a custom resolution, make sure that the UPPER PURPLE BOX is connected. 

If you want to use a preset resolution, make sure that the LOWER PURPLE BOX is connected.

Don't use clip_1 for prompting.

Use it, in this case, for LORA Triggers

High-Res fix settings (Tested on the same image):

- denoise: Use 0.5, 0.55, or 0.6. If you go lower you can get 
  segmentation (broken lines).

- steps: for best results use 20 - 30 steps. If you get some 
  segmentation, increase steps.

=================================================================
- Schedulers: from best to worse (very similar results within the same category)
a) normal 
b) simple, sgm_uniform 

The others don't work well (heavy segmentation).

=================================================================
- Samplers: from best to worse (very similar results within the same category)
a) deis, dpm_adaptive,
b) dpm_fast (good details), euler, 
c) uni_pc_bh2, heun, heunpp2, ddim, ipndm, dpmpp_2m, lms, dpm_2
d) lcm (very simple lines),

Broken: ancestrals, xxx_sde, ddpm, euler_cfg_pp, uni_pc

Only use nearest-exact.

scale_by 1.43: is the factor needed to upscale from 1MP to 2MP.

1) Load Image (Node): Just load your control image. Make sure it has the same dimensions ratio as that selected in text2img.

2) AIO Node: Choose your Pre-Processor. The first time you run it, it may take a while...it's downloading it from the internet.

3) Load the appropriate ControlNet model that matches your pre-processor.

4) Apply ControlNet (Node):

Canny (Pre = CannyEdge):             Set "end_percent" at exactly 0.300

Depth (Pre = DepthAnythingv2):       Set "end_percent" at exactly 0.400

HED (Pre = HED):                     Set "end_percent" at exactly 0.200

OpenPose (Pre = DW):                 Set "end_percent" at exactly 0.300

NOTE: Use Ctrl+B to toggle on/off a node.
segm/Anzhc Face seg 640 v2 y8n (no dill).pt
Select a node, then press ctrl+B to toggle "node bypass"
Select a node, then press ctrl+B to toggle "node bypass"

If you are using a segmentation model, use the sam options.

If you are using a bbox model, use the bbox options.

Also, use the denoise value to get the effect that you want, taking into consideration wether or not you are using a LORA with ADetailer.

FLUX RESULTIONS:

1MP: Use Preset resolution.

2MP: Choose "Upscale latent by" 1.43 (in the HighRes Fix Section).
